com.apriori.apt.reflect

Interface ArType

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArClass, ArGenericArrayType, ArParameterizedType, ArTypeVariable, ArWildcardType

    public interface ArType
    A interface that represents a generic type. Using implementors of this interface, information on generic type variables and even reifiable type parameters can be programmatically determined for processed type elements.

    This mirrors the Type interface, but is for representing types in source form for annotation processing vs. types in compiled form at runtime.

    See Also:
    Type, ArTypes

      • toTypeString

        String toTypeString()
        Returns a string representation of this type, suitable for constructing a representation of this type that could be used in Java source code. For most types, this is the same as toString(), but one glaring exception to that is in ArClass where toString() and toGenericString() return representations that resemble type declarations but toTypeString() returns a string that is a simple reference to the class's raw/erased type.
        Returns:
        a string representation of this type
